This paper deals with multi-label classification using community detection approaches from social networks to partition the label space. This involves machine learning techniques and algorithms, which are typically covered under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also deals with graph-based approaches and network analysis, which are covered under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which are covered under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The evaluation of the proposed approach involves comparing it with existing methods, which involves statistical analysis and experimental design, covered under cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves the use of graph-based approaches and algorithms, which are covered under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
